Boolean (bool) Data Types in Python :-

Defination :- 
    (i) We can use this data type to represent boolean values.
    (ii) The only allowed values for this data type are :- True and False
    (iii) Internally Python represents True as 1 and False as 0
         Eg. b=True
             type(b) 
             Output => bool
Example :-
    a=10
    b=20
    c=a<b
    print(c)
    Output => True
    True+True
    Output => 2
    True-False
    Output => 1

